ARGUMENT.

Farewell, Goddess: let the sea cease to bring back the dew into mine eyes or the breeze to echo my sighings; but may Thetis emulating thy bland look gaze placidly upon thee, and gently let the south wind breathe in thine ear. Let no bold wave heave himself high in Ocean and presume to come near to taste thy lip. Ah, my sear is that Love may affect both billow and breeze, and both rising high may trouble the main.
